               <p>MALCOLM CURRIE. On the 17th of May, about ten o'clock at night, I was opposite to Messrs. Coutts, in <placeName id="t18270531-239-crimeloc1279">the Strand</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270531-239-crimeloc1279" type="placeName" value="the Strand"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270531-239-crimeloc1279" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-239-off1277 t18270531-239-crimeloc1279"></join>. A person asked if I had lost my handkerchief. I felt and it was gone - he said they had run up a court. I gave him my address, and next morning he brought my handkerchief to me. I found the prisoner at the office.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182705310096"></xptr>ANGELIOUS BERTRAUN. On the 17th of May I was in the Strand, and saw the two prisoners going after several gentlemen; they then met the prosecutor nearly opposite Round-court, and I saw Wilkinson take the handkerchief from his pocket. I told Roberts (who was with me), to tell the gentleman; I watched them up a court. I saw them looking at the handkerchief under a gas-light, and McAndrew then put it into his hat.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270531-239-person1329">
                  THOMAS 
                  ROBERTS
               <interp inst="t18270531-239-person1329" type="surname" value="ROBERTS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-239-person1329" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-239-person1329" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoners behind Mr. Currie. I went to him - he gave me his address; we went down Round-court, and took the prisoners.</p>
               <p>McANDREWS' Defence. I met a young man who asked me to buy a handkerchief for 2s. 6d.</p>
               <p>WILKINSON'S Defence. I went up the court, and was taken - but am entirely innocent.</p>
               <p>McANDREWS - <rs id="t18270531-239-verdict1280" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270531-239-verdict1280" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 17.</p>
